## 4. Regra 2

<span style="color:#27ae60"><strong>Vogal + Y → + S</strong></span>

Quando o verbo termina em **vogal + Y**, acrescenta-se apenas **S**.

### Exemplo: TO SAY (dizer)

* I say
* You say
* <span style="color:#c0392b"><strong>He says</strong></span>
* <span style="color:#c0392b"><strong>She says</strong></span>
* <span style="color:#c0392b"><strong>It says</strong></span>
* We say
* You say
* They say

---

## 5. Regra 3

<span style="color:#8e44ad"><strong>Consoante + Y → remove Y + IES</strong></span>

Quando o verbo termina em **consoante + Y**, remove-se o **Y** e acrescenta-se **IES**.

### Exemplo: TO FLY (voar)

* I fly
* You fly
* <span style="color:#c0392b"><strong>He flies</strong></span>
* <span style="color:#c0392b"><strong>She flies</strong></span>
* <span style="color:#c0392b"><strong>It flies</strong></span>
* We fly
* You fly
* They fly

---

## 6. Regra 4

<span style="color:#16a085"><strong>Restante → + S</strong></span>

Para todos os outros verbos, acrescenta-se **S** na 3ª pessoa do singular.

### Exemplo: TO SPEAK (falar)

* I speak
* You speak
* <span style="color:#c0392b"><strong>He speaks</strong></span>
* <span style="color:#c0392b"><strong>She speaks</strong></span>
* <span style="color:#c0392b"><strong>It speaks</strong></span>
* We speak
* You speak
* They speak

